a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real and t :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. t x = abs (-3 + 2 * x)"
shows  "t (t (-4)) = 19"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 If $t(x) = |{-3+2x}|$, then what is $t(t(-4))$? The final Answer is 19
 ### Proof
 We have $t(-4) = |{-3 + 2(-4)}| = |{-11}| = 11$, so  \[t(t(-4))= t(11) = |{-3 + 2(11)}| = |{-3+22}| = \boxed{19}.\]
 *)

theorem
fixes x :: real and t :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. t x = abs (-3 + 2 * x)"
shows  "t (t (-4)) = 19"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Evaluate the function $t(x) = |(-3 + 2x)|$ when $x = t(-4)$. What is the final result? The answer is 19.
